      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be reported for key quantities of interest; GCI < 5% on fine grid.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted on the pump volute and impeller passage regions. Grid convergence index (GCI) was computed per Celik et al. (2008). GCI on the fine mesh was 2.8% for NIH and 3.4% for peak shear stress, both below the 5% threshold. The fine mesh of 4.2 million cells was adopted for all production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must be documented and traceable to the COU operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Bench validation experiments were conducted using porcine blood at 37°C with hematocrit 35 ± 2%. Flow rates of 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6 L/min at rotational speeds of 2500 and 3500 RPM were tested, fully spanning the CPB operating envelope. Temperature, viscosity, and inlet pressure boundary conditions were matched between experiment and simulation to within measurement uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metrics must be reported; predicted NIH values must fall within experimental uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "NIH predictions were compared against experimental measurements using the U-validation metric from ASME V&V 20. At all 5 operating points, predicted NIH fell within the expanded experimental uncertainty interval (k=2). The maximum prediction error was 8.3% at the 6 L/min, 3500 RPM operating point, within acceptable bounds for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoIs used in validation (NIH, RH) must be directly relevant to the COU decision (worst-case hemolysis identification).",
      "rationale": "NIH and the derived relative hemolysis index RH are the standard regulatory quantities for CPB hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance. These quantities directly govern the COU decision criterion (RH < 1 versus predicate device). No transformation or surrogate mapping is required between validated QoIs and decision QoIs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must address the same device geometry class, flow regime, and blood analog as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump, which shares the same impeller topology and volute geometry class as the subject device. Blood analog (porcine blood, matched hematocrit) and Reynolds number regime (Re 200–1800 in impeller passages) are consistent with the COU. Validation activities are assessed as sufficiently representative for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor; documentation of iterative convergence criteria is sufficient.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, formal numerical solver error quantification beyond iterative convergence monitoring is not required. Residuals were monitored to 1e-6 for all equations; mass imbalance was below 0.01% in all cases. This level of convergence documentation satisfies MRL 2 requirements without formal solver error assessment."
    },
