      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; analyst qualification records are sufficient.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, formal use error assessment is not required. The lead analyst holds a Ph.D. in biofluid mechanics with 8 years of CFD experience in cardiovascular devices. Simulation setup was reviewed by a second qualified analyst prior to production runs. Analyst qualification is documented in the project record."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; selection of turbulence and hemolysis submodels must be documented.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model and the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model were selected based on published literature for centrifugal blood pump CFD. Model form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2. Model selection rationale is documented in the simulation plan."
    },
    {
